definition.value: Growth of rubella virus in a culture derived from cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

label.value: Positive CSF treponema pallidum nucleic acid test

definition.value: Detection of Treponema pallidum (syphillis) nucleic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR) or reverse transcriptase (RT)-PCR.
Concentration of tetrahydrobiopterin in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) below the lower limit of normal.
The concentration of N-acetyl-aspartyl-glutamate (NAAG) in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is below the lower limit of normal.

label.value: Positive CSF Tropheryma whipplei bacteria microscopy

definition.value: The presence of antibodies in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) that react against a component of treponema pallidum (syphilis).
Increased autofluorescence in areas adjacent to the central macula (but not including the very center).

A condition in which the limbs of a fetus are immobile or held in a rigid position. The limbs are consistently immobile and rigid. Fixed extremities can be observed during prenatal imaging (e.g., ultrasound).

The density of the deep peripapillary microvascular network (i.e., the number of blood vessels) is below the lower limit of normal. This finding is observable by optical coherence tomography angiography.
Inflammation of the skin and soft tissues of the outer ear.
The pulsation of the superficial temporal artery cannot be detected on physical examination.

label.value: Displacement of the extensor tendon in metacarpophalangeal joint
Distortion of the anterior part of the interhemispheric fissure

definition.value: Growth of Actinomyces israelii (anaerobic filamentous gram positive) culture of lacrimal discharge or concretions.
An abnormal (positive) result of the Venereal Disease Research Laboratory (VDRL) test performed in peripheral blood, suggesting past or present syphilis.

label.value: Positive bloodstream rapid plasma reagin test

definition.value: Positive result of the the rapid plasma reagin test (RPR test. This is a rapid diagnostic test that looks for non-specific antibodies in the blood of the patient that may indicate an infection by syphilis or related non-venereal treponematoses.

label.value: Positive bloodstream HIV p24 antigen test
Tzanck smear with multinucleated giant cells
Positive bloodstream Tropheryma whippelii nucleic acid test

definition.value: Detection of nucleic acid of Tropheryma whippelii in the blood circulation by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR) or reverse transcriptase (RT)-PCR.
The amount of uroporphyrin in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label.value: Elevated circulating aspartate aminotransferase to alanine aminotransferase ratio

definition.value: Aspartate aminotransferase to alanine aminotransferase ratio increased greater than 1.5.
